{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review the UK\u2019s \u201cspecial relationship\u201d with the current US administration",
        "additional_details": "The UK has a long-standing \u201cspecial relationship\u201d with the United States involving extensive military, intelligence and diplomatic cooperation. When any US administration adopts policies that may increase global tensions or risk drawing allies into conflicts, the UK should independently review whether continued alignment serves our national interests. Parliament and the public should have transparency and oversight to ensure this relationship continues to benefit the UK\u2019s security and diplomacy.",
        "background": "Conduct a formal review of the UK\u2019s diplomatic, military and intelligence cooperation with the United States under the current US administration and report the findings to Parliament, including whether this relationship continues to serve the UK\u2019s national interest.",
